    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-03-05T22:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-03-05T22:13:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>247. Telegram 38065 From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Uganda</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d247fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, <gloss
                            target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> Uganda-US. Limited Official Use. Drafted by
                        Farnham (AFR/ESA) and <persName>Kinter</persName> (AF/E); cleared in AF/E,
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/AFR/ESA and <gloss target="#t_LAF1"
                            >L/AF</gloss>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_MCR1"
                            >Moore</persName>. Repeated to Addis Ababa, Dar es Salaam, London and
                        Nairobi.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d247fn2">The Department recommended moving
                        toward normal relations in a low key manner, avoiding public
                        statements.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1971-03-06T03:13:00+00:00">March 6, 1971, 0313Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>JOINT STATE/<gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> MESSAGE</p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT:</head>
                    <item>US/<gloss target="#t_GOU1">GOU</gloss> Relations: ProAgs</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>REF:</head>
                    <item>Kampala 641; State 27102</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Now consider it desirable to continue forward movement toward normalization
                    relations in low-key manner, avoiding public statements. Hope <gloss
                        target="#t_GOU1">GOU</gloss> will take similar view matter.</p>
                <p>2. Suggest that Embassy/USAID now begin move pending ProAgs forward for signature
                    by <gloss target="#t_GOU1">GOU</gloss> at appropriate levels. Prefer you start
                    with pending revisions of ProAgs already signed (Toronto Girls School,
                    Agricultural Co-Ops and IPA), following these with new ProAgs. Believe <pb
                        facs="d247-02" n="2" xml:id="d247-02"/> it preferable also to space ProAgs
                    out somewhat; rather than presenting simultaneously. If <gloss target="#t_GOU1"
                        >GOU</gloss> issues statement on revisions, we would reiterate that we
                    regard revision existing ProAgs as part normal working contacts. At that time
                    could reconsider whether proceed with new ProAgs.</p>
                <p>3. Among new ProAgs <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/W particularly interested
                    in signature those covering Agricultural Research Survey Team and Makerere
                    Graduate Agriculture Faculty as contractors already contacted and recruitment
                    underway. <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>: Realize Mission cannot issue
                    Makerere PIO/T until it receives <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/Wʼs
                    comments on proposed OPEX guidelines and final agreement on guidelines reached
                        <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>/W comments pouched March 4. In addition,
                    Chief Agricultural Research Officer PIO/T will need revision to bring it in line
                    with new guidelines. END <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>
                </p>
                <p>4. USAID should not include Livestock Production ProAg <pb facs="d247-03" n="3"
                        xml:id="d247-03"/> among first priorities for signature because contract
                    negotiations already underway for other projects and <gloss target="#t_FY1"
                        >FY</gloss>–71 deobs involved in Livestock ProAg amount. No objection,
                    however, if Mission prepares Livestock ProAg now for possible signature next
                    month.</p>
                <p>EXEMPT.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">Rogers</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
